A giant crocodile was spotted between some houses in Matsulu today, February 13. Some videos and pictures shared by a Facebook user of the name Mayidela Mathebula captured the creature. Some community members rushed to protect themselves from the reptile. They also suspect it had made its way to the area due to the overflowing rivers in Nkomazi.  Some citizens claimed their dogs are missing, and the crocodile could have consumed them. ALSO READ: Kruger Park floods: Some roads opened again Lowvelder approached the Mpumalanga Tourism and Parks Agency (MTPA) for comment. Its spokesperson, Kholofelo Nkambule, said an investigation is being conducted. “MTPA officials have reported that the reptile has gone back to the river.” She also urged the members of the public to be vigilant and to report similar matters immediately. “Should they encounter this animal again, they must immediately contact the officials who are experienced to handle them, at the Mpumalanga Tourism and Parks Agency,” Nkambule said.